		<td><b>Four colour theorem and NES graphics</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I didn't realise it until now, but there is a coincidence in the number of colours the NES can display with a single palette and the max. number of colours that is needed to distinguish arbitrary regions in a 2D plane.
<br />
<br />I'm not sure if this has any applications but I just discovered this coincidence and I'd like to know if anyone else ever noticed.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


