	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Use this knowledge to make an NES port of Balance of Power.</div>
<br />I mean this theorem doesn't apply only to countries on a map but can be generalized for any kind of 2D shapes.
<br />
<br />In other words, you can draw any set of shapes in a 2D plane with 4 colours, each shape being another colour than the shape next to it.
<br />
<br />I think this means you can draw anything on the NES, at least the shape of anything.

		

		</td>
